{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/2021/05/improving-your-video-setup","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"b7a07a24-9ea8-5f49-87f3-b63cf4429ce0","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/8ac56/desk-shot.webp 240w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/d3be9/desk-shot.webp 480w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/e46b2/desk-shot.webp 960w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/f992d/desk-shot.webp 1440w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/882b9/desk-shot.webp 1920w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/46261/desk-shot.webp 2400w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/09b79/desk-shot.jpg 240w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/7cc5e/desk-shot.jpg 480w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/6a068/desk-shot.jpg 960w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/644c5/desk-shot.jpg 1440w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/0f98f/desk-shot.jpg 1920w,\n/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/df51d/desk-shot.jpg 2400w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/6a068/desk-shot.jpg\"\n            alt=\"A desk with various items on it, including a microphone, a monitor and a DSLR as a camera.\"\n            title=\"A desk with various items on it, including a microphone, a monitor and a DSLR as a camera.\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p><audio controls src=\"https://anchor.fm/s/57ec5b10/podcast/play/33961175/https%3A%2F%2Fd3ctxlq1ktw2nl.cloudfront.net%2Fstaging%2F2021-4-21%2F5c4a8b46-38ea-a9e1-b8a0-f6e928eabd2d.mp3\" preload=\"metadata\" onplay=\"logPlay('improving-your-video-setup')\"></audio></p>\n<p>After a year of entirely virtual meetups and conferences, it seems unlikely at this point that we’ll ever go back to 100% in-person events. Like workplaces, most events seem to be leaning towards a hybrid model, with participants attending both in person, and virtually over a livestream. So with that in mind, what investments should you be making in your setup to ensure that when you choose to participate virtually, you’re not giving a sub-par experience to the people attending your talk?</p>\n<p>When reading the advice below, it’s important to remember that i’m coming at this from my perspective as a Developer Advocate. My job involves far more conference speaking than most, so it’s entirely possible that my setup is complete overkill for the majority of situations, but some people just like to invest in these things, so if you’re not into public speaking, but long for your Zoom game to be on point, then have at it, I’m not here to judge!</p>\n<h2 id=\"you-get-out-what-you-put-in\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#you-get-out-what-you-put-in\" aria-label=\"you get out what you put in permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>You get out what you put in</h2>\n<p>This is probably obvious, but up to a certain point, the more you spend, the better a result you’ll get. That isn’t to say you can’t lower the costs here and there, but the reality is that all these things should be considered an investment and the costs viewed accordingly. Where possible, I’ve included both expensive and cheaper options. I’ve used many of these at some point, so can stand over them, but where I haven’t had the chance to try something yet, I’ll mention that.</p>\n<h2 id=\"audio\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#audio\" aria-label=\"audio permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Audio</h2>\n<p>If you’re just starting out, audio is 100% where you should start. People will forgive poor video, but if they can’t hear you speaking clearly, then staying engaged with your content will be a real challenge.</p>\n<h3 id=\"higher-end-option---yeti-by-blue-130\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#higher-end-option---yeti-by-blue-130\" aria-label=\"higher end option   yeti by blue 130 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Higher end option - Yeti by Blue ($130)</h3>\n<figure class=\"float-left\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 150%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/8ac56/blueyeti.webp 240w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/d3be9/blueyeti.webp 480w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/e46b2/blueyeti.webp 960w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/f992d/blueyeti.webp 1440w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/882b9/blueyeti.webp 1920w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/0d890/blueyeti.webp 3662w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/09b79/blueyeti.jpg 240w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/7cc5e/blueyeti.jpg 480w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/6a068/blueyeti.jpg 960w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/644c5/blueyeti.jpg 1440w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/0f98f/blueyeti.jpg 1920w,\n/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/563e6/blueyeti.jpg 3662w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/8b47a4511f66b4c8cbaf27d3ecabace8/6a068/blueyeti.jpg\" alt=\"A Yeti by Blue microphone\" title=\"A Yeti by Blue microphone\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption><a href=\"https://www.bluemic.com/en-us/products/yeti/\">Yeti by Blue</a></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.bluemic.com/en-us/products/yeti/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Yeti by Blue</a> is almost a defacto standard now for people running smaller podcasts and is what I use. You can adjust the <a href=\"https://mynewmicrophone.com/microphone-gain\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">gain</a>, have different settings for one person using it versus multiple, you can mount it or have it on your desk, and easiest of all, it supports USB, so you don’t need a second piece of hardware to run it through.</p>\n<p>For a sense of what results the Yeti gives, every episode of <a href=\"/pages/podcast\">Klokta</a> was recorded using one, so feel free to check that out.</p>\n<h3 id=\"mid-range-option---snowball-by-blue-70\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mid-range-option---snowball-by-blue-70\" aria-label=\"mid range option   snowball by blue 70 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mid-range option - Snowball by Blue ($70)</h3>\n<p>At about half the price, the <a href=\"https://www.bluemic.com/en-us/products/snowball/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Snowball</a> is Blue’s “budget” option. I’ve never used it myself, but it’s well regarded and as the name implies, is from the same manufacturer as the Yeti, so has some similar benefits.</p>\n<h3 id=\"budget-conscious-option---the-mic-on-your-headphones\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#budget-conscious-option---the-mic-on-your-headphones\" aria-label=\"budget conscious option   the mic on your headphones permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Budget conscious option - The mic on your headphones</h3>\n<p>If you can’t afford to get a dedicated microphone, at a minimum you should use the microphone on your cellphone’s headphones. If you have AirPods or AirPods Pro, even better, use those. It’s moving the microphone a lot closer to your mouth, and the AirPods do fancy beam-forming things.</p>\n<h2 id=\"video\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#video\" aria-label=\"video permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Video</h2>\n<h3 id=\"higher-end-option---sony-a6400-w-sigma-prime-lens-and-elgato-camlink-4k-1300\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#higher-end-option---sony-a6400-w-sigma-prime-lens-and-elgato-camlink-4k-1300\" aria-label=\"higher end option   sony a6400 w sigma prime lens and elgato camlink 4k 1300 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Higher end option - Sony a6400 w/ Sigma Prime lens and Elgato CamLink 4K ($1300)</h3>\n<p>There’s no getting around the fact that $1300 is <strong>a lot</strong> for what you’d essentially be using as a webcam. But if you want to justify it to yourself, I’d point out that you can take it off the mount when you’re not presenting and you have a <em>very</em> good camera for taking photos of your kids, nature, friends etc.</p>\n<figure class=\"float-right\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/8ac56/a6400.webp 240w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/d3be9/a6400.webp 480w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/e46b2/a6400.webp 960w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/f992d/a6400.webp 1440w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/882b9/a6400.webp 1920w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/b33a3/a6400.webp 4032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/09b79/a6400.jpg 240w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/7cc5e/a6400.jpg 480w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/6a068/a6400.jpg 960w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/644c5/a6400.jpg 1440w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/0f98f/a6400.jpg 1920w,\n/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/d2602/a6400.jpg 4032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/80637f8ba50827ab8467cae82f1abd9d/6a068/a6400.jpg\" alt=\"A Yeti by Blue microphone\" title=\"A Yeti by Blue microphone\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption><a href=\"https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1453768-REG/sony_ilce_6400_b_alpha_a6400_mirrorless_digital.html\">Sony a6400 w/ Sigma Lens</a></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Anyway, this is definitely going to give you a serious step up from the built-in webcam you’re probably using. The <a href=\"https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1453768-REG/sony_ilce_6400_b_alpha_a6400_mirrorless_digital.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sony a6400</a> has super fast auto focus, an intuitive UI and a flip up LCD so you can position yourself. Pair that with a <a href=\"https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1234027-REG/sigma_302965_30mm_f_1_4_dc_dn.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">30mm Sigma Prime Lens</a> to give you that nice bokeh (blurred background) and you’re gonna look great.</p>\n<p>For an example of the kind of output you can expect, here’s a recording of an event I did that was pushed through Zoom then through Facebook, so you can imagine there’s a lot of compression going on and the result I think still looks pretty good. If you skip to around the 20 minute mark, my video is full screen and that will give you the best impression.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.07142857142857%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?height=314&amp;href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Ftechazmedia%2Fvideos%2F782304045823982%2F&amp;show_text=false&amp;width=560\" style=\"border:none;overflow:hidden; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allow=\"autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture; web-share\"></iframe> </div>\n<p>It’s a popular choice for Streamers, YouTubers and other video professionals, so there’s a wealth of information out there on how to configure it best, plus it’s widely supported. One last thing though. The a6400 apparently supports directly connecting over USB, but I was recommended to use an <a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/cam-link-4k\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Elgato CamLink 4K</a> and did so, but that could be a way to shave $120 off your costs.</p>\n<h3 id=\"mid-range-option---logitech-brio-199\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mid-range-option---logitech-brio-199\" aria-label=\"mid range option   logitech brio 199 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mid-range option - Logitech Brio ($199)</h3>\n<p>Coming in at just under $200, the <a href=\"https://www.logitech.com/en-us/products/webcams/brio-4k-hdr-webcam.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Logitech Brio</a> is still pretty pricey for a Webcam, but I’ve been told by those who own them (I do not) that the quality is top notch, as it pushes out 4K quality video.</p>\n<h3 id=\"budget-conscious-option---reincubate-camo-39-per-year\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#budget-conscious-option---reincubate-camo-39-per-year\" aria-label=\"budget conscious option   reincubate camo 39 per year permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Budget conscious option - Reincubate Camo ($39 per year)</h3>\n<figure class=\"float-left\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 59.583333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/8ac56/camo-example.webp 240w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/d3be9/camo-example.webp 480w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/e46b2/camo-example.webp 960w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/f992d/camo-example.webp 1440w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/882b9/camo-example.webp 1920w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/0160b/camo-example.webp 2784w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/8ff5a/camo-example.png 240w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/e85cb/camo-example.png 480w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/d9199/camo-example.png 960w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/07a9c/camo-example.png 1440w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/29114/camo-example.png 1920w,\n/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/6149e/camo-example.png 2784w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/png\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/4abbb57a5e7080909df12ea0c86860ad/d9199/camo-example.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of a recording that used Reincubate Camo\" title=\"A screenshot of a recording that used Reincubate Camo\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption><a href=\"https://reincubate.com/camo/\">Reincubate Camo</a></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>If you have an iPhone, then <a href=\"https://reincubate.com/camo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Reincubate Camo</a> is a great investment. For about a year I paired it with my iPhone XS and got really great results. It was a <em>vast</em> improvement from the <a href=\"https://www.logitech.com/en-us/products/webcams/c920-pro-hd-webcam.960-000764.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Logitech C920</a> I had.</p>\n<h2 id=\"lighting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lighting\" aria-label=\"lighting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lighting</h2>\n<p>Once you’ve settled on video and audio, you’re likely already in a good spot, but if you want to go further, the next thing I’d consider is <em>lighting</em>. I have two different lights I use when recording. Even one of these is going to be pretty good.</p>\n<h3 id=\"higher-end-option---elgato-key-light-199\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#higher-end-option---elgato-key-light-199\" aria-label=\"higher end option   elgato key light 199 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Higher end option - Elgato Key Light ($199)</h3>\n<figure class=\"float-right\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 78.75000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/8ac56/keylight.webp 240w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/d3be9/keylight.webp 480w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/e46b2/keylight.webp 960w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/87c73/keylight.webp 1353w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/09b79/keylight.jpg 240w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/7cc5e/keylight.jpg 480w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/6a068/keylight.jpg 960w,\n/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/26964/keylight.jpg 1353w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/da9c53304e27e8366f377ff7c736cfec/6a068/keylight.jpg\" alt=\"An Elgato Key Light\" title=\"An Elgato Key Light\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption><a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/key-light\">Elgato Keylight</a></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>I use a single <a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/key-light\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Key Light</a> clamped to my desk and offset to my right. The warmth of the light is adjustable from very bluish to very yellowish, and the output is adjustable from barely on to staring directly into the sun. It doesn’t get warm and has some nice touches like being controllable from my laptop (vs a physical button).</p>\n<h3 id=\"mid-range-option---generic-ring-lights-starting-from-10\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mid-range-option---generic-ring-lights-starting-from-10\" aria-label=\"mid range option   generic ring lights starting from 10 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mid range option - Generic Ring Lights (starting from $10)</h3>\n<figure class=\"float-left\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/8ac56/ringlight.webp 240w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/d3be9/ringlight.webp 480w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/e46b2/ringlight.webp 960w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/f992d/ringlight.webp 1440w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/882b9/ringlight.webp 1920w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/b33a3/ringlight.webp 4032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/09b79/ringlight.jpg 240w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/7cc5e/ringlight.jpg 480w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/6a068/ringlight.jpg 960w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/644c5/ringlight.jpg 1440w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/0f98f/ringlight.jpg 1920w,\n/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/d2602/ringlight.jpg 4032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/91d07eb03b751d7fa80c37d5e3bedb90/6a068/ringlight.jpg\" alt=\"A generic ring light\" title=\"A generic ring light\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption>Ring light</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>I originally started out with $50 ring light that I bought on Amazon. It’s since been discontinued, but Amazon has an almost unlimited supply of these things. What you’re looking for when considering them is </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Can you adjust the brightness? (Ideally yes)</li>\n<li>Is their a mount for your camera / phone built in? (Ideally yes)</li>\n<li>Does it plug into the wall or into USB? (I prefer USB, but this is personal preference)</li>\n<li>What size is it? (My one has an inner diameter of 8 inches and that feels about right)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"budget-conscious-option---sunlight-free-i-guess\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#budget-conscious-option---sunlight-free-i-guess\" aria-label=\"budget conscious option   sunlight free i guess permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Budget conscious option - Sunlight (free I guess?)</h3>\n<p>If you’re tapped out budget wise, but still look dark, consider if you can move your desk so that you face a window, because natural light can be pretty flattering. What you absolutely don’t want in the background is a large light source like a window or bright lamp. No amount of camera trickery will compensate well for that.</p>\n<h2 id=\"all-the-other-things\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#all-the-other-things\" aria-label=\"all the other things permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>All the other things</h2>\n<p>Once you’ve gotten all of the above sorted, you’re really into over-engineering for most situations. But I love a good gadget as much as the next person, so here’s a few other bits and pieces I use regularly</p>\n<figure class=\"float-right\">\n\t<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/8ac56/ipad-streamdeck.webp 240w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/d3be9/ipad-streamdeck.webp 480w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/e46b2/ipad-streamdeck.webp 960w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/f992d/ipad-streamdeck.webp 1440w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/882b9/ipad-streamdeck.webp 1920w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/0811d/ipad-streamdeck.webp 6000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/09b79/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 240w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/7cc5e/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 480w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/6a068/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 960w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/644c5/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 1440w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/0f98f/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 1920w,\n/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/857b3/ipad-streamdeck.jpg 6000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/b18a5027c916be372bff1cb9e49d6ea6/6a068/ipad-streamdeck.jpg\" alt=\"An iPad Mini running Stream Deck Mobile\" title=\"An iPad Mini running Stream Deck Mobile\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n\t<figcaption><a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/key-light\">Stream Deck Mobile</a></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/stream-deck-mobile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Stream Deck Mobile</a> ($25 per year): I had an old iPad Mini that wasn’t doing anything else, so I purchased Stream Deck Mobile and stuck it on a stand. It’s definitely helpful as you can configure it to control just about anything from Zoom to your lights, to playing random noises in meetings. If you don’t have a spare iPad or iDevice lying around, you can also buy a <a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/stream-deck\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">physical Stream Deck</a> for a significantly higher cost from Elgato.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.elgato.com/en/green-screen\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Elgato Green Screen</a> ($160): I really only pull this out for videos where I’ll do a bunch of post-production, but it’s a helpful tool, especially if you can’t really otherwise control your background due to space constraints etc. The screen shot in the “Reincubate Camo” section above involved the green screen.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.fully.com/standing-desks/jarvis/jarvis-hardwood-standing-desk.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Jarvis Hardwood Standing Desk</a> (starts at $1139): You’re going to need somewhere to put all this stuff obviously, and I put mine on a Jarvis hardwood desk. It’s adjustable over a wide range and is big enough to hold everything comfortably.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"the-content-is-still-the-star\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-content-is-still-the-star\" aria-label=\"the content is still the star permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The content is still the star</h2>\n<p>The choices I’ve made in terms of equipment reflect what works for me and I’m sure many others have made equally valid choices, both more expensive and cheaper. It’s important to remember though, that at the end of the day, video and audio equipment are just tools to help make your content shine. But if that content isn’t polished to start with, no amount of fancy lenses or shiny lights will make it interesting. Be sure you invest the time and effort there before you worry about how you look or sound.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2021/05/improving-your-video-setup","tagSlugs":["/tag/developer-relations/","/tag/working-from-home/","/tag/gadgets/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-05-25T12:00:00.121Z","description":"It's been over a year now, and hybrid/remote events are here to stay. Here's some suggestions on what tools you can invest in to level up your video conference setup so every event you do hits that professionalism bar you want.","tags":["Developer Relations","Working from home","Gadgets"],"title":"Improving your video conference setup","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/86f90dcc62ac476576fde0e138e5a2dd/desk-shot.jpeg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2021/05/improving-your-video-setup"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1503789672","251939775","401334301"]}